//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_ark_abjure}

NOTE: This operation formally renounces an
{rbtga_ark}
from
{rbtgi_repository}
by enumerating and deleting every package beneath the ark's
hallmark subtree via the GAR REST API implemented by
{gar_service}.

An
{rbtga_ark}
is the coherent unit of a Recipe Bottle build: a set of packages rooted at
`{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/«HALLMARK»/` and distinguished by basename.
The
{rbtga_ark_image}
(basename `image`) contains the container image itself.
The
{rbtga_ark_about}
(basename `about`) contains SBOM and build metadata.
The
{rbtga_ark_vouch}
(basename `vouch`) contains verification results.
The
{rbtga_ark_pouch}
(basename `pouch`) contains the build context (conjure/bind only, absent for graft).
A fifth basename, `diags`, is present for conjure arks only (build-time diagnostics forwarded to the about pipeline).
For conjure vessels, a single `attest` package holds per-platform tags (`attest:«HALLMARK»-«ARCH»`).
Abjuring an ark deletes every package discovered beneath the hallmark subtree as a single logical operation.

The
{rbtr_director}
abjures an ark:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtga_ark}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_VESSEL»` provided as first argument (retained for AAK signature compatibility; not used to construct the subtree path, drops in AAL)
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_HALLMARK»` provided as second argument
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if hallmark missing: "Hallmark parameter required"

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtga_hallmark}
. *Validate Hallmark Format*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_HALLMARK»` matches pattern `[cbg]\d{12}-r\d{12}` (mode prefix + dual timestamp)
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if malformed: "Hallmark format invalid"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Construct Hallmark Subtree*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«SUBTREE»` as `«HALLMARKS_ROOT»/«INPUT_HALLMARK»/` where `«HALLMARKS_ROOT»` derives from `RBGL_HALLMARKS_ROOT` (kindled to `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«REPO_BASE»` as the GAR REST API repository base (`projects/«PROJECT»/locations/«REGION»/repositories/«REPOSITORY»`)

//axhos_step
. *Enumerate Packages Under Subtree*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/list[GAR REST API: packages.list] with:
... method: `GET`
... endpoint: `«REPO_BASE»/packages?pageSize=1000`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. Extract `.packages[].name` from the response, strip the resource prefix, and URL-decode `%2F` back to `/`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«ARK_PACKAGES»` as the list of decoded package names whose prefix equals `«SUBTREE»`
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if `«ARK_PACKAGES»` is empty: "No packages found under «SUBTREE» — hallmark not present in registry"

//axhos_step
. *Confirm Abjuration*:
.. {rbbc_show}
"Will abjure «COUNT» packages under «SUBTREE»:" followed by each entry in `«ARK_PACKAGES»`
.. {rbbc_require}
user types `yes` to confirm
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if not confirmed: "prompt not confirmed."

//axhos_step
. *Delete Each Enumerated Package*:
.. For each `«PACKAGE»` in `«ARK_PACKAGES»`:
... {rbbc_store}
`«ENCODED»` as `«PACKAGE»` with `/` replaced by `%2F`
... {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/delete[GAR REST API: packages.delete] with:
.... method: `DELETE`
.... endpoint: `«REPO_BASE»/packages/«ENCODED»`
.... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
... {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response (deletion returns a long-running operation; the 200 is treated as accepted)
... {rbbc_fatal}
if delete fails: "Failed to delete package «PACKAGE» (HTTP «STATUS_CODE»)"

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtga_ark}
. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
"Hallmark abjured: «INPUT_HALLMARK» («COUNT» packages)"
.. For each deleted package:
... {rbbc_show}
`  - «PACKAGE» deleted`

//axhoc_completion
Procedure completes successfully when every package discovered beneath the hallmark subtree has been deleted from the registry and the abjuration confirmation is displayed.
The ark is now formally renounced and no longer part of the repository corpus.
Because enumeration drives the delete set, there is no separate existence check and no orphan-detection branch: whatever lives in the subtree is removed, and an empty subtree is itself the "not present" signal.
Deleting a package removes all of its tags in one call — per-basename HEAD/DELETE dances are no longer required.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_image_delete}

NOTE: This operation jettisons a single image tag from
{rbtgi_repository}
using the Docker Registry HTTP API V2 implemented by
{gar_service}.

`rbfl_jettison` is locator-generic: the same procedure backs
{rbtga_ark}
hallmark members,
reliquary tool images, and enshrinement images.
The package path embedded in the
{rbst_locator}
selects the domain — the procedure itself does not branch.

NOTE: To delete an entire {rbtga_ark} (the full `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/«HALLMARK»/` subtree — every basename including `image`, `about`, `vouch`, and any `pouch`/`diags`/`attest` tags present), use {rbtgo_ark_abjure} instead.

NOTE: Jettisoning an interior member of a reliquary subtree (e.g., a single tool image) leaves a hole in an otherwise-coherent set. The operator accepts this piecemeal-by-image semantic; recovery is nuclear: re-run {rbtgo_depot_inscribe} to restore the full reliquary corpus. The operation provides no integrity guard against such interior holes.

The
{rbtr_director}
jettisons an image by {rbst_locator}:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbst_locator}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_LOCATOR»` provided as first argument in `package-path:tag` format
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if missing: "Locator parameter required (package-path:tag)"
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if malformed (no colon): "Invalid locator format. Expected package-path:tag"
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PACKAGE_PATH»` as portion before the final colon (e.g., `{gar_hallmarks_namespace}/«HALLMARK»/image`, `{gar_reliquaries_namespace}/«STAMP»/syft`, `{gar_enshrines_namespace}/«ANCHOR»`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«TAG»` as portion after the final colon
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if `«PACKAGE_PATH»` is empty: "Package path is empty in locator"
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if `«TAG»` is empty: "Tag is empty in locator"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Confirm Jettison*:
.. {rbbc_show}
`Will jettison: «INPUT_LOCATOR»`
.. {rbbc_require}
user types `yes` to confirm
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if not confirmed: "prompt not confirmed."

//axhos_step
. *Jettison Tag*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://github.com/opencontainers/distribution-spec/blob/main/spec.md#deleting-tags[Docker Registry API: DELETE manifests] with:
... method: `DELETE`
... endpoint: `«REGISTRY_BASE»/«PACKAGE_PATH»/manifests/«TAG»`
... header: `Authorization: Bearer «DIRECTOR_TOKEN»`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 202 (Accepted) or 204 (No Content) response
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if jettison fails: "Jettison failed with HTTP «STATUS_CODE»"
.. NOTE: V2 DELETE-by-tag has producer-side asymmetric semantics. For single-platform pushes (`docker push`), the tag points to a single image manifest; DELETE removes it, the package becomes empty, and GAR drops the package container from `ListPackages`. For multi-platform pushes (`docker buildx --push`, `skopeo copy --all`), the tag points to an OCI image index referencing N per-platform child manifests; DELETE removes only the index, leaving the N children as untagged orphan content. The package container persists in `ListPackages` because it still holds those untagged child manifests.
.. NOTE: The orphan-children residue is reclaimed autonomously by the depot's GAR cleanup policy — see {rbtgo_depot_levy} step *Create Container Repository* for the policy install, schema-verification sources, and cadence semantics. User-facing display surfaces ({rbtgo_hallmark_tally} and {rbtgo_image_rekon}) filter out packages with zero live tags, so tooling output reflects the correct post-jettison state immediately even though GAR-side reclamation is lazy. External observers querying GAR REST `ListPackages` directly will see the walking-dead package container until the cleanup policy's next run.

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbst_locator}
. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
`Jettisoned or nonexistent: «INPUT_LOCATOR»`

//axhoc_completion
Procedure completes successfully when the tag has been jettisoned from the registry and the jettisoned message is displayed.
The locator-generic shape means a hallmark member, a reliquary tool image, or an enshrinement image are all deleted by the same call — domain identity lives in the locator's package path, not in branched logic.
